{"path":"C:\development\repos\thegame\docs\theme.md","file_text":"# TreeID - LinkittyDo Theme Guide

## Overview
TreeID uses the **LinkittyDo** visual identity: a playful mid-century/retro aesthetic with bold typography, simple geometric shapes, strong contrast, and soft drop-shadows. The nature theme adds earthy greens and woodland tones while maintaining the core brand palette.

---

## Color Palette

### Primary Colors (LinkittyDo Core)
| Token | Hex | Usage |
|-------|-----|-------|
| `--ld-cream` | `#FDEC92` | Warm background, card fills |
| `--ld-mint` | `#A9EAD2` | Accent panels, success states |
| `--ld-ink` | `#161813` | Primary text, outlines |
| `--ld-pop` | `#FB2B57` | CTAs, alerts, wrong answers |
| `--ld-paper` | `#EEEDE5` | Off-white highlights, cards |

### Nature Extension (TreeID Specific)
| Token | Hex | Usage |
|-------|-----|-------|
| `--ld-forest` | `#2D5A3D` | Correct answers, tree-related accents |
| `--ld-bark` | `#8B6914` | Evidence tiles, earthiness |
| `--ld-leaf` | `#7CB342` | Leaf evidence, spring season |
| `--ld-autumn` | `#E67E22` | Autumn season, warmth |
| `--ld-winter` | `#95A5A6` | Winter season, bare branches |

### Supporting Neutrals
| Token | Hex | Usage |
|-------|-----|-------|
| `--ld-muted-green` | `#5E6554` | Disabled states, secondary text |
| `--ld-tan` | `#A29A61` | Tertiary backgrounds |
| `--ld-blush` | `#E7A790` | Soft highlights |

---

## Typography

### Font Stack
```css
--font-headline: 'Luckiest Guy', 'Bungee', cursive;
--font-ui: 'Nunito', 'Inter', sans-serif;
--font-mono: 'JetBrains Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
```

### Type Scale
| Name | Size | Weight | Usage |
|------|------|--------|-------|
| `--text-hero` | 3rem (48px) | 700 | Game title, big numbers |
| `--text-title` | 2rem (32px) | 700 | Screen titles |
| `--text-heading` | 1.5rem (24px) | 600 | Section headers |
| `--text-body` | 1rem (16px) | 400 | Body text, descriptions |
| `--text-small` | 0.875rem (14px) | 400 | Captions, hints |
| `--text-tiny` | 0.75rem (12px) | 400 | Labels, badges |

### Text Styling
- Headlines use `letter-spacing: 0.05em` and text-shadow for depth
- Body text uses `line-height: 1.6` for readability
- Important labels get `text-transform: uppercase`

---

## Spacing & Layout

### Spacing Scale
```css
--space-xs: 0.25rem;  /* 4px */
--space-sm: 0.5rem;   /* 8px */
--space-md: 1rem;     /* 16px */
--space-lg: 1.5rem;   /* 24px */
--space-xl: 2rem;     /* 32px */
--space-2xl: 3rem;    /* 48px */
```

### Border Radius
```css
--radius-sm: 4px;
--radius-md: 8px;
--radius-lg: 16px;
--radius-xl: 24px;
--radius-round: 50%;
```

### Shadows
```css
/* Soft drop shadow (cards, panels) */
--shadow-soft: 0 4px 12px rgba(22, 24, 19, 0.15);

/* Hard shadow (buttons, interactive elements) */
--shadow-hard: 4px 4px 0 var(--ld-ink);

/* Inset shadow (pressed states) */
--shadow-inset: inset 2px 2px 4px rgba(22, 24, 19, 0.2);
```

---

## Component Patterns

### Buttons
```css
.btn-primary {
  background: var(--ld-pop);
  color: var(--ld-paper);
  border: 3px solid var(--ld-ink);
  border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-hard);
  font-family: var(--font-headline);
  font-size: var(--text-heading);
  padding: var(--space-md) var(--space-xl);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: transform 0.1s, box-shadow 0.1s;
}

.btn-primary:hover {
  transform: translate(-2px, -2px);
  box-shadow: 6px 6px 0 var(--ld-ink);
}

.btn-primary:active {
  transform: translate(2px, 2px);
  box-shadow: 2px 2px 0 var(--ld-ink);
}
```

### Cards / Panels
```css
.card {
  background: var(--ld-paper);
  border: 3px solid var(--ld-ink);
  border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft);
  padding: var(--space-lg);
}

.card-accent {
  background: var(--ld-mint);
}
```

### Evidence Tiles (Face-down)
```css
.evidence-tile {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--ld-forest) 0%, var(--ld-bark) 100%);
  border: 3px solid var(--ld-ink);
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-hard);
  aspect-ratio: 1;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.evidence-tile:hover {
  transform: scale(1.05);
}

.evidence-tile.revealed {
  background: var(--ld-paper);
}
```

### Tree Profile Card
```css
.tree-profile {
  background: var(--ld-cream);
  border: 4px solid var(--ld-ink);
  border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft);
  padding: var(--space-xl);
  text-align: center;
}

.tree-silhouette {
  background: var(--ld-paper);
  border: 3px dashed var(--ld-muted-green);
  border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
  min-height: 200px;
}
```

---

## Iconography

### Style Guidelines
- Use simple, bold line icons (3px stroke)
- Rounded line caps and joins
- Consistent 24x24 or 32x32 viewBox
- Color with CSS (currentColor)

### Evidence Icons
- 🍂 Leaf: simplified leaf outline
- 🌳 Bark: vertical texture lines
- 🌰 Seed: acorn/cone shape
- 🌿 Bud: small branch with buds
- ❄️ Winter: bare branch silhouette
- 🗺️ Range: US outline with region highlight
- 📍 Habitat: landscape thumbnail

---

## Animation Guidelines

### Transitions
```css
--transition-fast: 0.1s ease-out;
--transition-normal: 0.2s ease-out;
--transition-slow: 0.4s ease-out;
```

### Motion Principles
- Use `transform` for performance (not `left`/`top`)
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`
- Evidence tile flips: 0.4s with 3D transform
- Score increments: countup animation
- Success/failure: subtle shake or pulse

### Card Flip Animation
```css
.flip-card {
  perspective: 1000px;
}

.flip-card-inner {
  transition: transform var(--transition-slow);
  transform-style: preserve-3d;
}

.flip-card.flipped .flip-card-inner {
  transform: rotateY(180deg);
}
```

---

## Responsive Breakpoints

```css
--bp-mobile: 480px;
--bp-tablet: 768px;
--bp-desktop: 1024px;
--bp-wide: 1280px;
```

### Layout Adaptations
- **Mobile**: Stack evidence tiles in 2x4 grid, full-width species list
- **Tablet**: 4x2 evidence grid, side panel for candidates
- **Desktop**: Full layout with evidence grid, tree card center, candidate list right

---

## Dark Mode (Future)

Reserved tokens for potential dark mode:
```css
--ld-dark-bg: #1A1C18;
--ld-dark-surface: #2D2F2A;
--ld-dark-text: #E8E6E1;
```

---

## Usage Examples

### Correct Answer State
- Background flash: `var(--ld-forest)` with white text
- Check icon appears
- Points animate upward

### Wrong Answer State
- Background flash: `var(--ld-pop)` with white text
- X icon appears
- Shake animation on card

### Focus Points Display
- Use leaf icons for remaining points
- Gray out (var(--ld-muted-green)) when spent
- Pulse animation when revealing evidence
